\b \ul NEW EXTERNALS
\b0 \ulnone \
\

\fs24 	
\b cv.jit.blobs.*
\b0  : this series of externals performs a number of analysis function on individual blobs (connected components) labeld by cv.jit.label.\
\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.bounds
\b0 : finds bounding box for each blob.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.centroids
\b0 : finds centroids and mass for each blob.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.direction
\b0 : estimates the direction each blob points to.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.elongation
\b0 : measures each blob's elongation (thinness).\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.moments
\b0 : calculate moments of inertia, Hu invariants, centroids and mass for each blob.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.orientation
\b0 : finds the main axis for each blob.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.recon
\b0 : estimates the statistical distance between each blob and a trained model.\
	
\b cv.jit.blobs.sort
\b0 : assigns blobs labels that do not easily change from frame to frame.\
\
	
\b cv.jit.canny
\b0 : extract edges.\
	
\b cv.jit.faces
\b0 : finds human faces. (Not available for pre-Jitter 1.6 version on Mac.)\
	
\b cv.jit.features
\b0 : finds high-contrast, easy-to-track areas.\
	
\b cv.jit.hough
\b0 : computes Hough space from edges.\
	
\b cv.jit.learn
\b0 : perform pattern recognition.\
	
\b cv.jit.lines
\b0 : find straight lines.\
	
\b cv.jit.ravg
\b0 : compute the running average over time. (Essentially duplicates 
\b jit.slide 
\b0\fs26 but gives more accurate output with char input.)\
\
